channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden to award Medal of Honor to Union soldiers in 'one of the earliest special operations' in Army history
item.description: President Biden is to posthumously award the Medal of Honor to two Union soldiers who stole a Confederate train during the Civil War and then destroyed railroad tracks and telegraph lines.

item.title: House GOP Ad: VP Harris 'Biden's Enabler in Chief, Architect of Border Crisis'
item.description: With Democrats fighting among themselves about whether President Joe Biden should continue to be the party's presidential nominee, the House Republicans' campaign arm is turning its attention to Vice President Kamala Harris.

item.title: Dark Tech, Dark Harvest: Categorizing the Democratsâ€™ Hidden Tech Network
Criticisms mount that Biden is a 'shadow' of himself after disastrous debate: 'Not the same man' from VP era
item.description: President Biden is facing fierce concern and criticism following his disastrous debate performance, which stands in stark contrast to his demeanor as vice president.

item.title: Missouri AG Bailey Petitions Supreme Court on NY Election Interference
item.description: Missouri Attorney General Andrew Bailey has filed a lawsuit petitioning the Supreme Court for a declaration that prosecutors in the state of New York's business records case against former President Donald Trump inferred with the presidential election.

item.title: LEAKED: Absolute Panic Sets in for Democrats on Donor Call, 'Comatose or Dead Biden' Leads to Desperation
Obama cautiously advises Biden after shaky debate performance, looming rematch with Trump: report
item.description: Despite showing support and encouragement for his once VP, former President Barack Obama is reportedly concerned about Biden's road to re-election following his poor debate performance.

item.title: Kremlin: No Dialog With Trump About War, Peace
item.description: There is no dialog between Russia and Donald Trump about the war in Ukraine, the Interfax news agency reported Wednesday, citing the Kremlin's spokesman.

item.title: Ludicrous: Elizabeth Warren Believes It's a Good Idea to Push for Higher Taxes During Election Season
Democratic donors unsure if Biden campaign can continue: reports
item.description: Fundraisers and top donors are in disagreement whether President Biden's reelection campaign will be able to defeat former President Donald Trump following last week's debate.

item.title: Reuters/Ipsos: Only Michelle Obama Bests Trump as an Alternative to Biden
item.description: Former first lady Michelle Obama is the only hypothetical presidential candidate alternative that can beat presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump, a post-debate Reuters/Ipsos poll found.

item.title: Biden Can't Even Keep the Courts Straight Anymore - Check Out the Confused Post He Just Deleted
Biden blames European trips for debate flop, despite long huddle at Camp David: 'Almost fell asleep onstage'
item.description: President Biden is now attributing his rocky debate performance to a busy June travel schedule, saying at a fundraiser that he "almost fell asleep onstage."

item.title: Judge Greatly Limits Biden's Rule Protecting LGBTQ+ Students
item.description: Enforcement of a federal rule expanding anti-discrimination protections for LGBTQ+ students has been blocked in four states and a patchwork of places elsewhere by a federal judge in Kansas.
